# 1.  ===========================================

# ReadStockFile() 
# Argus: 
#   stock_num: 
# Return: 
#   a data.table of 5 columns
#     type chr,  chr,  chr,  num,  int 

ReadStockFile <- function(stock_num)
{
  #  ---------------------
  assert_that(stock_num %in% stock_list)
  
  #  ------------------------
  tryCatch(
    {
      dt <- read.csv(
        file.path("csvStockFiles", paste0(stock_num, ".csv")),
        header = TRUE,
        sep = ";",
        colClasses = c(rep("character", 3), "numeric", "integer")
      ) %>% as.data.table()
      message("", stock_num)
      
    },
    error = function(e) {message(""); e}
  )
  
  
  #  ----------------------------
  dt[, DateTime := as.POSIXct(paste(TDate, MinTime), format = "%Y%m%d %H%M", tz = "PRC")]
  dt[, TDate := as.Date(TDate, "%Y%m%d")]
  dt[, return := c(NA, diff(EndPrc)/EndPrc[-.N])]  # 
  message("")
  
  setkey(dt, "DateTime")
  
  return(dt)
}



# 2.   ======================================
# CheckStockData()
# Arugs:
#   dt: data.table from last step
# Return:
#   cleaned data.table

CheckStockData <- function(dt) 
{
  #  ----------------------------
  tryCatch(
    {
      if (uniqueN(dt) == nrow(dt)){
        message("")
      } else {
        dt <- unique(dt)
        message("")
      }
    },
    error = function(e) message("")
  )
  
  # ----------------------------
  #  4*60+1 = 241 
  tryCatch(
    {
      checktime <- dt[, .N, by = TDate][N != 241]
      if (nrow(checktime) == 0) {
        message("")
      } else {
        message("")
        print(checktime)
      }
    },
    error = function(e) message("")
  )
  
  return(dt)
}




# 3.   ======================================
# AnalysisDis()/or
# Argus
#   dt: 
#   what: "return" or "MinTq"
#   when = c(in_start, in_end, out_start, out_end): /
#      2015-01-05
#      34

AnalysisDis <- function(dt, what = "return", 
    when = c("2015-01-05", "2015-12-31", "2016-01-04", "2016-01-29"))
{
  #  --------------------------
  when <- as.Date(when)
  assert_that(
    what %in% c("return", "MinTq") && length(what) == 1,
    length(when) == 4,
    when[1] < when[2] && when[2] <= when[3] && when[3] < when[4]
  )
  # / --------------------
  # (all >= 0) 
  # retrun, 
  # 
  dt_in <- 
    dt[TDate >= when[1] & TDate <= when[2], what, with = FALSE] %>% 
    unlist(use.names = FALSE) %>%
    abs() %>%
    log()
  dt_out <- 
    dt[TDate >= when[3] & TDate <= when[4], what, with = FALSE] %>% 
    unlist(use.names = FALSE) %>%
    abs() %>%
    log()
  
  dt_in_g <<- dt_in  # just for debugging
  dt_out_g <<- dt_out
  
  # /retrun/Vol---------------------
  # R boxplot()
  # histogram,
  
  boxplot(dt_in, dt_out, 
          xlab = "in sample         out of sample",
          main = sprintf("distribution of log(abs( %s )) of stock %s", what, stock_num),
          outline = FALSE)
  
  return(0)
}

# out-sample 80% quantile,,
# buy or sellsignal.
# ,
# out-of-sample ,,
# 90% 80%quantile .
# 
# 5%2%
# ===================================================================


rm(list = ls())

require(data.table)  
require(magrittr)  
require(ggplot2)
require(assertthat)  
require(stringr)  

load("dt.Rdata") # load Rdata

Trade <- function(
  dt, 
  quantile = 0.9,  #  90% quantile 
  sell = 0.05,  # 5%
  stop = 0.02,  # 2%
  when = c("2015-01-05", "2015-12-31", "2016-01-04", "2016-01-29")
)
{
  # / --------------------------------------
  when <- as.Date(when)
  dt_in <- dt[TDate >= when[1] & TDate <= when[2]]
  dt_out <- dt[TDate >= when[3] & TDate <= when[4]]
  
  #  --------------------------------------
  #reutrn,return & Volumn 
  # return0ie. 10% quantile
  # Volumn Volumn 
  q1 <- (1 - quantile) / 2
  q2 <- 1 - q1
  q <- quantile(dt_in$return, probs = c(q1, q2))
  q_up <- q[2]
  q_down <- q[1]
  
  # 
  buypoint_index <- which(dt_out$return < q_down | dt_out$return > q_up)
  dt_buysignal <- dt_out[buypoint_index][, .(DateTime, Signal = "BuyPoint")]
  dt_trade <- merge(dt_out, dt_buysignal, by = "DateTime", all = TRUE)
  dt_trade[is.na(dt_trade)] <- ""  # SignalNANA==
  
  #  ------------------------------------------------
  # 
  # out sample, 
  #  
  # 5%2%
  # 
  
  state <- 0  # 01
  sellpoint <- NaN  # 
  stoppoint <- NaN  # 
  for (i in 1:nrow(dt_trade)) {
    
    if (state == 1) { # 
      
      if (dt_trade[i, EndPrc] > sellpoint) {
        dt_trade[i, Close := "Sell"]  # sellpoint, sell
        state <- 0
      } else if (dt_trade[i, EndPrc] < stoppoint) {
        dt_trade[i, Close := "Stop"]  # stoppoint, stop
        state <- 0
      } else {dt_trade[i, Close := ""]}
      
    } else {  # (state == 0) # 
      
      if (dt_trade[i, Signal == "BuyPoint"]) {
        dt_trade[i, Buy := "Buy"]
        state <- 1
        buyprice <- dt_trade[i, EndPrc]
        sellpoint <- buyprice * (1 + sell)
        stoppoint <- buyprice * (1 - stop)
      }
      
    }
    message("Looping ", round(i/nrow(dt_trade)*100), " % ...") # 
  }
  dt_trade[is.na(dt_trade)] <- ""  # SignalNA
  
  # 
  stoptime <- nrow(dt_trade[Close == "Stop"])
  selltime <- nrow(dt_trade[Close == "Sell"])
  totalreturn <- selltime * sell - stoptime * stop
  message("Total return is ", totalreturn, " Sell: ", selltime, " Stop: ", stoptime)  
  
  return(dt_trade)
}


#  ======================================================

dt_trade <- Trade(
  dt, 
  quantile = 0.9,
  sell = 0.04,
  stop = 0.02,
  when = c("2013-06-01", "2014-12-31", "2015-01-01", "2015-02-01") 
)

dt_trade[, index := seq_along(DateTime)]

  xlab("date index")
